<TITLE> EC overturns 30 cancellations on appeal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 6 (bdnews24.com)The Election Commission on Saturday overturned its decision on 30 previously cancelled nominations, declaring the candidacies valid, as the first day's hearing of appeals concluded. "The commission has heard 80 appeals against cancelled nominations till 10pm," said EC deputy secretary AKM Salimullah. "Of the appellants, nominations of 30 candidates have been declared legal." Almost as many, 27 appeals against cancellations, were rejected, said the deputy secretary. "Sixteen hearings were suspended and the verdict on seven appeals will be given later," he said. The commission began hearings on appeals against cancelled nominations earlier in the day. Some 268 appeals against cancellation of nominations, and 35 appeals against the EC's validation of candidacies, had been submitted up to 10pm Saturday. Among the appellants, at least 15 had nominations cancelled on grounds of bill default. The hearings began at around 11am at the conference room of the EC Secretariat, in the presence of chief election commissioner ATM Shamsul Huda and two other commissioners M Sakhawat Hussain and Muhammed Sohul Hussain. A total of 557 nominations were initially rejected by the EC. Some 1,899 of a total of 2,456 nominations filed were found valid after the two days of scrutiny on Dec 3-4. Dhaka seats saw the most cancellations, while independent candidates had the largest number, 188 nominations, annulled. Of party candidates, Jatiya Party nominations saw the most rejected59, followed by BNP52, Awami League35 and Jamaat-e-Islami3. Prospective candidates whose nominations were rejected, or anyone objecting to nominations accepted by the EC, have up to Dec 7 to appeal. The hearings will continue till Dec 10, not including Eid day on Dec 9. The last day for withdrawal of candidacy is Dec. 11. The deadline for submission of nomination papers was Nov. 30. bdnews
